Roasting peppers in the oven gives them a slight char that's perfect inside fajitas. Paired with homemade refried beans, citrusy sour cream, and fresh cilantro, these fajitas are bound to be a hit.

Preheat the #oven{} to 400 degrees. Core, seed, and remove the white ribs from the @Red Bell Pepper{1} and @Yellow Bell Peppers{1}, then thinly slice. Chop the @Cilantro{¼%ounce} leaves and stems, keeping both separate. Halve, peel, and finely dice @Red Onion{1}(finely diced). Drain and rinse the @Kidney Beans{13.4%ounce}.

Toss the bell peppers on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon} and a pinch of @Salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}. Place in the oven for about ~{15%minutes}, until soft and slightly charred.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pot{} over medium heat. Add the diced onion and cook, tossing for ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened. Add the beans, @Southwest Spice Blend{1%teaspoon}, cilantro stems, @water{¼%cup}, and @Hot Sauce{1%teaspoon} (to taste) to the pot. Season with salt and pepper. Cover and cook for ~{10%minutes}, then coarsely mash with a #fork{}.

Meanwhile, zest, then halve the @Lime{1}. In a #small bowl{}, combine the @Sour Cream{2%ounce}, a pinch of lime zest and a squeeze of lime juice, to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Warm the @Flour Spinach Tortillas{4}: Wrap the tortillas in #tin foil{} and place in the oven for ~{5%minutes} to warm.

Assemble the Roasted Pepper Fajitas: Everyone can assemble their own fajitas with the tortillas, beans, roasted bell peppers, citrus sour cream, and cilantro leaves. Enjoy!